  "text": "Globally, altered pattern of PRMT6 in PCa mimics that of SMYD3, another HMT which targets different aminoacidic residues [CITATION_1] . Although no significant associations with standard clinicopathological parameters were depicted, either in our series or TCGA dataset, PRMT6 overexpression associated with shorter interval to biochemical recurrence, suggesting that it imparts a more aggressive phenotype. Interestingly, PRMT6 transcript and protein levels were globally concordant, although no significant differences were depicted between scores +2 and +3. This is most likely due to the semi-quantitative nature of immunohistochemical scoring, which may not be able to discriminate among subtle, yet biologically significant, differences in protein levels. Indeed, mRNA quantitation is more objective and may better discriminate tumors with different biological and clinical aggressiveness, as demonstrated for SMYD3 [CITATION_2] .",
